According to the General SVR Telegram channel, purportedly run by a Kremlin insider, a report sent to Putin stated that it has "not been possible to create the minimum comfortable conditions for the life of people in the occupied territories of the Luhansk region". The report added that in a number of settlements there is no gas and water supply, that residents of Severdonestk "cook food on the street" and "wash in the lake" and that there is a "putrid smell in the streets". The General SVR Telegram channel stated that Putin "ignored the report" and added that now is the time to "address these issues". FOLLOW BELOW FOR LIVE UPDATES... 